\begin_layout Subsection
Changes in Estimates
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The estimate used for depreciation calculations might change as time the
 asset it used.
 In such case, the change affects only future calculations (no retroactive
 adjustment).
 For example, extending the asset useful life decreases the depreciation
 expense.
 It should be asked, whether there is a real reason for this change (or
 is it an earnings management).
\end_layout

